{
  "doc_id": "27441",
  "text": "In addition, another subgroup of obesity has been defined, variously referred to as \"metabolically obese but normal weight\" or \"metabolically unhealthy normal weight\" (MUNW) [CITATION_1] . This group, in contrast to the MHO group, displays the typical obesity related metabolic disturbances of hyperinsulinemia, premature insulin resistance, hypertriglyceridemia, and possibly elevated risk of developing diabetes and CVD [CITATION_2] . There are few studies examining vascular inflammation or hepatic steatosis (HS) explicitly in this population.",
